{"abstract": "The abrupt rise and increasing success of activist investors are forcing big money managers to reassess their traditionally passive role as shareholders.", "web_url": "https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/03/18/new-alliances-in-battle-for-corporate-control/", "snippet": "The abrupt rise and increasing success of activist investors are forcing big money managers to reassess their traditionally passive role as shareholders.", "lead_paragraph": "For ages, institutional investors like mutual funds and pension funds were content to take stakes in public companies, trust their managements and bet on long-term gains. Companies trusted that these investors would be passive shareholders and not rock the boat.", "print_section": "B", "print_page": "1", "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [{"rank": 0, "subtype": "jumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2014/03/19/business/0319ACTIVIST/0319ACTIVIST-jumbo-v2.jpg", "height": 403, "width": 514, "subType": "jumbo", "crop_name": "jumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "superJumbo", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2014/03/19/business/0319ACTIVIST/0319ACTIVIST-superJumbo-v2.jpg", "height": 403, "width": 514, "subType": "superJumbo", "crop_name": "superJumbo", "legacy": {}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "thumbnail", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2014/03/19/business/0319ACTIVIST/0319ACTIVIST-thumbStandard-v2.jpg", "height": 75, "width": 75, "subType": "thumbnail", "crop_name": "thumbStandard", "legacy": {"thumbnail": "images/2014/03/19/business/0319ACTIVIST/0319ACTIVIST-thumbStandard-v2.jpg", "thumbnailwidth": 75, "thumbnailheight": 75}}, {"rank": 0, "subtype": "thumbLarge", "caption": null, "credit": null, "type": "image", "url": "images/2014/03/19/business/0319ACTIVIST/0319ACTIVIST-thumbLarge-v2.jpg", "height": 150, "width": 150, "subType": "thumbLarge", "crop_name": "thumbLarge", "legacy": {}}], "headline": {"mai